A Nyeri tycoon accused of orchestrating his son's murder will remain in custody for five more days to allow police complete investigation. 

Stephen Wang’ondu Kinini and four other suspects were arrested earlier this week over the murder of Daniel Mwangi. 

Mwangi was killed last month outside his house in Mweiga. 



